I previously tried the Ainsworth in midtown and wrote a not-so-awesome review. My friend persuaded me one night to come here to watch the game and grab a bite, so I gave it a chance.  Compared to the other location, this one is great. I can't believe that they are related.  The food here was solid American fare. The portions are not small, and well cooked. We ordered some wings and a flatbread as an app, tacos and burger as the mains. The flatbread was nicely cooked, crispy bottom, and abundant in toppings. Wings were a smaller portion than I would have liked.  For the main courses, they were well portioned. the taco shells were supposed to be soft but they were crispy because they were over-fried. Otherwise, well made tacos. Burger & Fries were also well cooked.  Only note: We sat at the bar and the bartender was drinking wine and vaping on the job. NOT awesome service in that respect.
